## R2: Spec-Implementation Synchronization Report

**Report ID**: R2  
**Generated**: 2026-06-12  
**Status**: ✅ Complete

### Executive Summary

Scanned the AutoForge codebase and spec ledger, then reconciled statuses to restore the specs as the single source of truth. Many top-level specs carried stale `draft`/`proposed` headings while the implementation was already complete. Conversely, several specs claimed full implementation for features that are only partial (Relay visualization, multi-provider dispatch, `bring_in` handoff).

### Actions Taken

| Category | Action | Count |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Stale specs | Deleted `backend/auto-forge/*.ad` placeholder stubs | 7 files |
| Status scrub | Updated `architecture.ad` heading statuses to match body/code | 8 items |
| Status scrub | Downgraded over-claimed goals (G10.x, G11.x, G17, G13) | 9 items |
| Status scrub | Upgraded `D19` API source config to `implemented`, `D20` to `in_progress` | 2 items |
| Empty modules | Filled `auth/goals.ad`, `auth/module.ad`, `auth/tests.ad` | 3 files |
| Empty modules | Filled `i18n/*.ad` (goals, module, architecture, designs, plans, tests) | 6 files |
| Duplicates | Merged duplicate `Chat-G10` entries; set status to `implemented` | 1 item |
| Consistency | Updated `Chat-A1`/`Chat-D1` delete-all-sessions statuses | 2 items |
| Backlog | Documented remaining gaps in `Auth-G2/G3` | 2 goals |

### Key Findings

**Implemented but underspecified:**
- RBAC/auth integration is live in `main.rs`, `App.vue`, and `useAuth.ts`.
- i18n framework is operational with `en` + `zh` locales.
- API source configuration UI and CRUD endpoints exist.

**Specs overstate implementation:**
- Relay node-graph animation, cost breakdown, and specs-touched panels are partial.
- 3-zone responsive layout lacks Zone-C context drawer.
- Ctrl+K jump-to-ID shortcut is bound but has no dialog.
- Multi-provider auto-dispatch and fallback chain are not wired.

**Genuinely missing:**
- `bring_in` baton-style chat-to-relay handoff.
- Semantic/RAG search in wiki.
- AutoDown WYSIWYG / spec-aware templates.
- Fine-grained RBAC permission enforcement on forge/relay routes.
- `ContextManager` / `PermissionPolicy` integration into chat/tool path.

### Remaining Recommended Work

1. Continue module-by-module status scrub for per-module spec files.
2. Add `Relates to:` cross-links between module IDs and consolidated IDs.
3. Implement or formally defer P0 gaps (`bring_in`, multi-provider dispatch).
4. Add a spec linter to catch heading/body status drift automatically.
